      "suggested_fix": "Remove from Tier 1. Move to Tier 3 as 'Structured Data Viewer' requiring backend preprocessing with human-verified mappings or explicit document type markers from the ingest pipeline. Fallback must be the original official PDF, never client-side HTML mutation of legal text."
    },
    {
      "severity": "critical",
      "location": "Global: Accessibility Compliance",
      "description": "Gap analysis completely omits WCAG 2.1 AA compliance, which is a legal requirement for government-facing tools in Brazil (Decreto 7.724/2012) and most jurisdictions. No mention of screen reader support for the 'mobile reading' experience, focus management for the Command Palette, or ARIA labels for the floating TOC. The 'Resume reading' feature without SR announcement will disorient blind users. This is a production blocker, not a QoL item.",
      "suggested_fix": "Add Tier 1 item: 'Accessibility Audit & ARIA Implementation'. Include focus trapping for modals, heading navigation for screen readers (complementing visual TOC), and live regions for the IntersectionObserver section detection. Test with actual screen readers on mobile (VoiceOver/TalkBack)."
    },
    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Tier 1.1: Mobile Reading System",
      "description": "Resume reading strategy using localStorage will fail at scale. localStorage has a ~5MB limit; storing scroll positions, section IDs, and timestamps for a research tool with heavy usage will hit quota errors, crashing the persistence layer silently. Additionally, IntersectionObserver on 30,000-word documents without virtualization will cause severe performance degradation on 6-inch mobile devices due to massive DOM weight.",
      "suggested_fix": "Replace localStorage with IndexedDB (via idb-keyval or similar) for reading history. Implement virtualization (react-window or native CSS content-visibility) for the document renderer to keep DOM nodes under 50 regardless of document length. IntersectionObserver should only watch sentinel elements, not all headings."
    },
    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Tier 2.3: PDF Export",
      "description": "Strategy to proxy PDFs from in.gov.br assumes a 1:1 mapping between the tool's document IDs and the official DOU URL scheme that may not exist or may be unstable. If the tool modifies/cleans HTML (as implied by the 'safe-HTML renderer'), the official PDF will not match the user's viewed content, creating citation errors where lawyers cite paragraph numbers that differ between the two versions.",
      "suggested_fix": "Add a 'Content Fidelity Warning' when showing the PDF fallback indicating that the official PDF may differ from the processed view. Implement server-side PDF generation from the processed HTML to ensure WYSIWYG citation accuracy, or clearly brand the official proxy PDF as 'Unformatted Original' vs 'Enhanced View'."
    },
